column5: Anyone seen these? My bud caught one down in the southern states, I was in awe. First one I've ever seen.  Not as pretty as a bluegill but interesting (at least to me) nonetheless
100% Green Sunfish. Native to SW Ontario and a small portion of NW Ontario
Never heard of em. Thanks. This was caught in the southern states. Cool looking fish
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Warmouth  It looks like a hybrid to me?
Big mouth + super aggressive + turquoise lines on the face/gill plate = green sunfish.
Green sunfish. Love em. One of the most beautiful fish in our waters.
